{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e7110b03-0e69-4f5f-85ed-b87b07bb30db","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the TFM:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run `dotnet restore` and `dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check for any NuGet packages with major version bumps or breaking API changes in the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4f4dd2e2-9581-40ac-93cc-e588878f5e34","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward guidance question — I don't need to search any codebase or run tools. I can answer directly.","outputTokens":281,"requestId":"6C3E:2D7D24:E835D5:10FD1A2:69FE9333"},"id":"762438b5-d000-40bd-a73c-14d71af6790e","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:51:54.430Z","parentId":"24f9bf4f-8e62-4a72-8461-4bd7b02cf4e9"}
